164382],"slug":"maimai-dx-universe-plus","summary":"Updated release of maimai DX UNiVERSE.\n\nGeneral Information / Changes:\n\"Invitation Play\" introduced, where another player can play the BASIC difficulty of the song being played on the unused side of the cabinet for free (once per day).\n- If both have cleared the song (80% or above), the player who initiated the invitation gets a boost in Area progress as well as a 1.5x Ticket.\n- FULL SYNC badges and Collections that require 2 players cannot be obtained in Invitation Play.\n\n2-player mode now awards an extra stamp in Stamp Cards.\n\nWhen choosing Tour Members in Areas:\n- Locking is reintroduced.\n- \"Auto set\" now lets you choose between ascending and descending order of Tour Members' level.\n\nArea progress is now shown on the music select screen, along with the current ticket and DX Pass.\n\nFULL SYNC status is now shown during gameplay.","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/maimai-dx-universe-plus","videos":[{"id":140533,"video_id":"WJkW8MTXYKA"},{"id":140534,"video_id":"zvAF0mNomkM"},{"id":140535,"video_id":"LRouvsVKsE0"}],"websites":[{"id":712003,"url":"https://www.sega.jp/arcade/detail/maimai-deluxe-universe-plus/","type":{"id":1,"type":"Official Website"}},{"id":712004,"url":"https://silentblue.remywiki.com/maimai_DX:UNiVERSE","type":{"id":2,"type":"Community Wiki"}},{"id":711892,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maimai_(video_game_series)","type":{"id":3,"type":"Wikipedia"}}]}